# LICENSE

This project incorporates multiple licenses due to the varied nature of its components and their respective requirements. The primary license for the project is the Affero General Public License (AGPL), while certain components or libraries used within the project are licensed under the MIT License.

## Affero General Public License (AGPL)

The majority of this project is licensed under the AGPL. This includes all the custom code written specifically for this project that does not fall under the exemptions mentioned below.

The AGPL license ensures that all modifications and derived works of AGPL-licensed code are also made available under the AGPL when distributed over a network. For full license text, see [AGPL-LICENSE.md](./AGPL-LICENSE.md).

For information on obtaining the source code for AGPL-licensed parts of the project, please refer to the project's documentation or the [source code repository](https://github.com/tnware/Proxmox).

## MIT-Licensed Components

This project utilizes components/libraries that are licensed under the MIT License. These components are used as-is or have been modified to fit the needs of this project.

- **Proxmox VE Helper-Scripts**: Base repository for this fork. For the original library and its license, visit their [GitHub Repository](https://github.com/tteck/Proxmox).

The MIT License is permissive and allows these components to be used within AGPL-licensed projects. It requires that the original copyright and license notice be included with any substantial portions of the software.

## Obtaining Source Code

The AGPL license requires that the source code be made available to users who interact with the software over a network. To obtain the source code of AGPL-licensed parts of this project, please visit [our repository](https://github.com/tnware/Proxmox).

For any further questions regarding licensing or to obtain specific parts of the source code, please reach out to the project maintainers.